\n<Guild Master>Ouch! Did Lynx die? That guy was quite the earner, or
rather, he was a big help. Man, we lost a good one!

\n<Guild Master>You'll have to work hard for both your share and theirs,
\n[1]! I'm counting on you all!

\n<Guild Master>Hey there, \n[1]. You seem to use some interesting
techniques, but you're still lacking in practical
experience, right? Don't get too carried away, okay?

\n<Guild Master>You start with the lousy jobs. That's the proper order.
Don't let your guard down even if it's just slimes.
\n<Guild Master>Hey, how was your first job?
It was tough.
It was a piece of cake.

\n<Guild Master>I see! Well, if you get tired, reset with a drink! Huh? You
can't handle alcohol?

\n<Guild Master>Hahaha! The late Lynx said the same thing after his first
job.

\n<Guild Master>I appreciate you working hard. I'm also looking for
information on your sister. Just be patient, alright?

\n<Guild Master>A bit of a lewd talk, but if the reward is 10000G, you get
60%, and I get 40%. It's a mediation fee, you know?

\n<Guild Master>Well, I'll let you drink booze or milk for cheap in return!
No complaints, okay?

\n<Guild Master>If you want to level up, keep repeating the quest on the far
left. Monsters spawn like idiots there.

\n<Guild Master>Hey \n[1]. Your twin is also working hard. Really helps me
out.

\n<Guild Master>What's this about always getting into lewd situations? What
are you talking about? Only succubi showing up? Eh? Humans
too?
\n<Guild Master>That's what you call a lucky streak. Good for you.

\n<Guild Master>Suddenly a flood of requests came in, right? Some are
specifically asking for you, so make sure you take care of
them. Good luck!

\n<Guild Master>\n[1]... could you occasionally check on... the orphanage?
It seems that Radlo guy has gone missing.

\n<Guild Master>I try to help the kids as much as I can. I owe a lot to the
previous Mama.

\n<Guild Master>It's really good that you didn't catch Radlo. The fact that
he's "L" is a secret. Don't tell anyone.

\n<Guild Master>Also, about the Howling Stone. It's a real pain to sell that
stuff. I'm looking for an appraiser now.

\n<Guild Master>By the way, that Noblesse guy asked for an escort again.
Well, just do whatever with requests from such crappy
nobles, okay? Don't go all out.

\n<Guild Master>Deasnte...? A literal translation... I don't get it.
Probably the guy who wrote it doesn't understand either.
Pfft. All ancient script, huh? More than just a hassle.

\n<Guild Master>Hey, hey, don't put a piano here? We don't need music in
this bar. Seriously, what kind of power are you using? It's
kinda scary.

\n<Guild Master>Ho, you use a bow too? Quite skillful. Let's put an apple on
Dodon's head and see if you can aim for his face, alright?

\n<Guild Master>Poison Bullet? Did you steal that from an enemy? \n[1]
really is a genius. The fact that I hired you means I have
good judgment. So that makes me a genius too, right?

\n<Guild Master>Hm? That bomb... where have I seen it... Ah, no, never mind.
That's another story. It's not very powerful, is it?

\n<Guild Master>What's that? An advance notice from "L"? Ah, right, the
previous one also... nah, never mind.

\n<Guild Master>You're equipped with a Fire Magic Book? For you, that's
quite a basic piece of equipment. You can use flashier magic
than that.

\n<Guild Master>What's up? You're wearing lipstick. Is the little one trying
to be sexy? Well, uh... hmm. (Trying to grow up fast?)

\n<Guild Master>What's up? You're wearing lipstick. No, I mean, it's an era
of diversity so I'm not saying anything... (But you look
completely like a girl now.)

\n<Guild Master>Hm? Charm magic? Huh? It comes out of your butt? Ah... well,
cats do have the cutest tails.

\n<Guild Master>That magical power... could it be something Lynx left
behind?...

\n<Guild Master>When you work here for years, you see members come and go
many times. You become numb to feeling happy or sad about
it.

\n<Guild Master>But I haven't forgotten a single one of them. Even if they
were using fake names.

\n<Wanz>...\n[1], you sometimes glance at my boobs or big sis's

\n<Siebel>I heard Lynx died having sex with a monster. That guy was an
idiot about that kind of stuff, huh? Well, it's better than
dying in pain, right?

getting yourself caught up in it would be the worst.
Adventurers have to be a bit cold-hearted, or they'll die
young.

\n<Seibel>But the children are feeling even lonelier. I try to check

tiny kitten! Hahaha! Guess I really need to get serious
about training.

\n<Dodon>Hey, hey, is it true that Lynx is dead? That guy was one of
the top three in this guild in terms of skill. Guess that
makes me number three now, huh.

\n<Dodon>Just kidding. Well, adventurers tend to die just like that
when their time comes.

\n<Dodon>So Latier squeezed you to death all the way in Kunes? How

\n<Dodon>I mean, what's so good about living, right? Just drinking

\n<Kunes>\n[1], huh? How does it feel to become an adventurer?
You're the youngest one here. But remember, it's not about
seniority.

\n<Kunes>It's the strong ones who are truly remarkable. I've been

\n<Kunes>Humanoid demons, huh... I've heard they've become more

\n<Kunes>It's a shame about Lynx, but I'm glad you're safe. He died

\n<Kunes>Damn it... I just can't shake that scene from my mind...
It's sickening...
\n<Kunes>No, it's nothing... Nothing at all...

\n<Kunes>So that Latier managed to escape at the last second, huh?

\n<Kunes>Are you getting used to adventuring? Don't push yourself too

\n<Kunes>Without that guy around, there's no competition. Hurry up
and get stronger so you can be on par with me.

\n<Kunes>You've equipped the Fire Magic Book, huh? That'll give you

effective against the undead. Remember that.

\n<Kunes>Equipped with a dagger, are you? Slash attacks are the same

\n<Kunes>Huh? You can do martial arts too? Seems like you can do

\n<Kunes>Is that stone Lynx's barrier? I see... He discarded his

\n<Kunes>Hey, hey! Stop with the charm! I'm still pretty shaken up

\n<Kunes>Oh, that chocolate pie looks delicious! Let me have a

\n<Annie>Maybe the mother's spirit is still lingering. Either her

\n<Annie>Hmm. Sorry! I don't know how to help. Or maybe, making the

\n<Annie>Right now the mother's heart is probably holding it back,

Like slinging stones. Despite its cute appearance, it's a

\n<Annie>What's with that stinky lunchbox! It smells just like the

\n<\n[1]>It's long been numb. To the point where I smell nothing at

\n<Rintei>A succubus, huh? Their combat strength isn't all that
impressive. If you take the initiative and behead them, it's
an easy victory. However...

\n<Rintei>Still, there's a certain resistance to cutting them down
since they take on a human form. That must be what they're
aiming for...

\n<Rintei>The Demon Lord has created quite the troublesome monsters.
Creatures that attack the mind...

\n<Rintei>Lynx... He had a weakness for women. I hope at least he
passed without suffering.

\n<Rintei>You must be the rumored beast-person. It's very rare to see
one around here. This town has poor security, so please be
especially careful at night.

\n<Rintei>Thank you for avenging Lynx and Kunes. Those two were my
benefactors.

\n<Rintei>When I had just arrived in these slums, all I could do was
study. They trained me in combat... and taught me how to
live as an adventurer.

\n<Rintei>Well then, I should also get to completing requests. There
are surprisingly some jobs that require brains. Adventurers
are jacks-of-all-trades, after all.

\n<Rintei>Sister practicing necromancy...? Why would she do such a
thing... It's hard to understand. It's hard to believe,
given her personality...

\n<Rintei>It's not that I doubt you. However, as a resident of Driane,
I've known her longer. There probably aren't many who would
trust you over her.

\n<Rintei>It seems you've been fulfilling requests as an adventurer.
Helping people in need brings a sense of fulfillment that
isn't just about money, doesn't it?

\n<Rintei>But to survive here, money is of utmost importance. Make
sure to find jobs that are worth your while and do your
best.

\n<Rintei>Hmm...? That stone is... no, it's not a stone, is it? A
clump of wind barrier? I see, Lynx's...

\n<Rintei>He was skilled at wind barrier techniques. He would create a
shield on the spot with a barrier and then strike during the
opening. He had an interesting way of fighting.

\n<Rintei>This brings back memories. Is that weapon possibly imbued
with Lynx's magical power? Even in death, some things
continue to persist.

\n<Rintei>He died soon after meeting \n[1], but if he had lived, I'm
sure they would have become good friends. Please make good
use of that magic power.

\n<Rintei>Line lightning, huh? It's a magic with excellent rapid-fire
and piercing capabilities. It should give you a considerable
advantage against water attribute opponents. It should even
penetrate water barriers.

\n<Rintei>Oh, floating thunder orbs... impressive indeed. A thunder
strike with its launch speed suppressed has extremely high
energy efficiency.

\n<Rintei>Huh! \n[1]-san, you fight with your fists? With four hands,
you can go "ora ora"! I'm envious. Eh? You don't know "ora
ora"?

\n<Rintei>Is that proliferation liquid? It's meaningless to equip it
yourself. It would be better to have your back hands hold
it.

\n<Rintei>To be able to handle a bow as well. You've surpassed the
realm of mere dexterity. Goodness, I wonder what kind of
training you've undergone.

\n<Rintei>Charm magic... It seems to be highly effective on creatures
with low intelligence... but, it won't work on me! (Please
don't let it work! I beg you!)

\n<Rintei>Hm? Something smells good. Is that... a lunch plate? Ah,
it's today's lunch. Looks delicious.

\n<Lynx>Ah, the new twins, huh? I'm Lynx. Nice to meet you. The
Master was really off-putting at first, right? That's just
how they are with everyone.

\n<Lynx>But once you get on their good side, they'll treat you well.
It's like that exclusive camaraderie you find in the slums,
you know? Anyway, they're not a bad person.
B

\n<Lynx>Jobs are first come, first served, so sometimes you overlap
with others.

\n<Lynx>Especially treasure hunting is popular. You go there only to
find someone's beaten you to it and left nothing behind.

\n<Lynx>The worst is when adventurers start fighting over the loot.
People can be most cruel when money's involved. I find that
kind of hassle not worth it, so I just let it go.

\n<Lynx>A real adventurer is someone who's content with enough money
to drink and occasionally bed a woman.

\n<Rakura>That Lynx bastard... tch. In the end, I never managed to get
back at him for running off with the win. My magic couldn't
break through his barrier technique even once.

\n<Rakura>I wield lightning, and he had wind. The elemental affinity
was against me... But still, I wanted to get back at him
just once.

\n<Rakura>This guild is a bit special, you see. We get requests from
"above." They're sarcastically called "Heaven's Blessings."

\n<Rakura>It means "the jobs those living the good life above don't
want to do" get passed down to us. We're at the very bottom
of the adventurer's guild.

\n<Rakura>"Kunes used to say 'The strong are the ones who are
respected,' but true strength is surviving to the end. An
adventurer's strength isn't just about power."

\n<Rakura>"A truly strong adventurer is one who survives no matter
what. Even if they're dirty or pathetic, the one who stands
till the end is the one who's respected."

\n<Rakura>"Megna, that succubus... you're the one who let her escape,
right? Did you take her down? Good job. If you had killed
her the first time, there would have been fewer victims."

\n<Rakura>"You get it? Normally, it's taboo to even ask for a
monster's name. Don't talk to them. Don't show mercy. Don't
give them an opening."

\n<Rakura>"Succubi are at the bottom of the barrel when it comes to
combat ability. If you don't get seduced, you can finish
them off with a single strike. You're too soft. Remember
that."

\n<Rakura>"You're starting to get a bit of awareness as an adventurer,
aren't you? If you make a name for yourself, maybe your
sister will catch wind of your rumors. The day you'll meet
is bound to come."

\n<Rakura>"You let that succubus Megna escape? Why do you know her
name? With those kinds of creatures, you should be cutting
off their heads before any conversation happens."

\n<Rakura>"Don't exchange words with monsters. The more human they
look, the harder it is to kill them, but that's exactly the
strategy of the demon race. No matter how strong you are, as
an adventurer, you're second-rate."

\n<Rakura>"Have you started to take your role as an adventurer
seriously? Do you have your dog tag? It's a hassle if no one
can identify you when you drop dead."

\n<Rakura>"If you find the body of an adventurer, feel free to use
their belongings. To receive their effects is to carry on
their will. If you can afford it, bury them or take them
back with you."

\n<Rakura>"Oh, that's Line Lightning. Magic that rapidly fires thin
bolts of lightning. Lightning attacks penetrate, so they're
strong against groups and shield bearers. It might be hard
for someone with your fire and wind attributes to handle
though."

\n<Rakura>"Floating Thunder Orb, huh? You've got some rare magic
there... Normally lightning would fly at high speed, but
this magic deliberately keeps it suspended in the air. It's
quite a difficult spell, but you're doing well with it."

\n<Rakura>"Poison Gas Bullet? What's that disgusting magic? Did you
learn that from the succubus Megna? You're seriously a
genius."

\n<Rakura>"Roughly Zero Degrees? What kind of magic is that? Almost
freezing at 0C? Try a little harder."

\n<Rakura>"Oh, that's a fire magic tome. Magic that suits your own
attribute really hits differently, doesn't it? It's basic
but fundamental. I'm of the lightning attribute myself, but
I think fire is cool too."

\n<Rakura>"Huh? You use Charm? Isn't that ineffective against succubi?
Might be more effective against humans though."

\n<Rakura>"You've got quite an old flame magic tome there. Did you
pick it up from a garbage dump? Even though it's so
tattered, it still works properly, huh?"

\n<Rakura>"Fighting by throwing pianos? Are you out of your mind?
Apologize to music."

\n<Rakura>"I can feel the power of wind. It makes me remember Lynx.
Well, sooner or later I'll have to go meet him too. That's
the life of an adventurer after all."

This is a manual on combat. (Close with Cancel)
Controls
Status Ailments
Normal Attack (Physical Damage)
Seduction Attack (Stamina Damage)
Easy Mode
Challenge

Z key: Confirm/Press and hold for fast-forwarding events X
key: Cancel/Open menu
A key: Fire attacks D key: Hold to lock direction

Q key: Auto text advance/Change character in equipment
screen SHIFT: Walk/Shorten defeat scene animations Ctrl:
Fast skip

Certain attacks may cause status ailments. Please check the
status displayed in the upper left corner.

Heat: Ammo -1, Combat power down by 20% (Heart Mark)
Weakness: Combat power halved (ATK Down Mark) Paralysis:
Unable to attack (Zap Mark)

Slow: Fire rate halved (time it takes to shoot) (Downward
Arrow) Poison: Lose 2% HP at certain steps (Poison Mark)
Deadly Poison: Lose 4% HP at certain steps (Different Color
Poison Mark)

Status ailments can be cured by walking a certain number of
steps or using the herbal medicine item. They can also be
prevented by certain equipment.

Normal attacks (such as those that shoot fire or lightning)
will damage your health (HP). If your health reaches 0, you
will be defeated.

There are seven types of attack bullets: "Fire," "Water,"
"Lightning," "Slash (Wind)," "Blunt," "Temptation," and
"Food (Poison)."

The protagonist can reduce specific types of damage by
equipping items such as clothes. (Example: Fire clothes cut
fire damage by 20%)

Additionally, certain attacks are more effective against
certain enemies. Choosing the type of attack for your weapon
can give you an advantage in battle.

When attacking, refer to the "Combat Power" status. If the
enemy's defense is high or if there is a bad compatibility
with the attack type, it will display as miss (0 damage).

Some weapons may have a low hit rate, which will also result
in a miss.

If an enemy touches you or tempts you, you will continue to
take damage to your stamina (SP) until you shake them off.
If your stamina reaches 0, you will ejaculate and be
defeated.

If you are being tempted by a succubus or similar enemy, you
may also lose experience points at the same time. Escape as
soon as possible.

The defeat scene changes depending on which attack caused
you to ejaculate. Try to find all the different ways to
lose. This will result in a game over.

By selecting Action Easy from the options menu, enemy
attacks will become less intense and easier to handle.

You can switch even during combat, so if you find it
difficult, it is recommended to switch to Easy Mode.

Also, when Action Easy is ON, a relief treasure chest will
appear at the inn. There is no disadvantage to using it.

You can fight an enemy again by accepting their quest again
even after defeating them once. In some quests, Challenge
Mode will be added.

In Challenge Mode, you fight under various restrictions and
receive special rewards for winning. The restrictions are
chosen from the following:

"Premature Ejaculation (SP1)," "No Damage (HP1)," "No Cat
Borrowing," "Menu Forbidden (No item or skill use)," "Half
Health and Stamina," "Protagonist Attack Forbidden (Fight
with only cat borrowing)"

Clearing Challenge Mode does not affect progress. It's an
element for completionists, so feel free to ignore it or
proceed with it as you wish.

This is a guide on Karma value. (Close with
Cancel)\C[14]Current Karma Value\v[270]
About Karma Points
If you make bad choices

Karma value (morality) increases with good deeds and
decreases with bad deeds. (It decreases if you let a
succubus escape.)

Choices that affect Karma will be displayed in color. Also,
even if an H-scene occurs, the game will not end and you can
continue. Let me give you an example. (It doesn't change
regardless of the choice you make)
\C[10]Give in to temptation Karma -1
\C[1]Defeat them Karma +1

Karma value affects the content of conversations and the
ending. If you make a good choice, the request form will
glow blue, and if you make a bad choice, the request form's
light will turn red.

If you make the wrong choice, you can redo the request to
change the outcome.

If you make a bad choice, such as letting a succubus escape,
it may increase the difficulty of later events or result in
more victims.

However, by going to the place of the succubus you let
escape, you can see special H-scenes like Energy Drain.
There is no benefit to sacrificing levels.

In the case of a succubus, you can go to their location by
selecting "Go to see" from the red request form.\C[14]"Go to
see"\C[0]

For characters in town, please go see them directly. Giving
them money might lead to something good. (Or it might not)
